//! creating this intermediate reference is itself **Undefined Behavior (UB)**.
//!
//! Rust 1.95 stabilized the raw reference operators `&raw const expr` and `&raw mut expr`,
//! which **directly create raw pointers**, bypassing intermediate references, thus completely avoiding this problem.
//!
